Purpose:

This folder contains all ViewHolder classes.
ViewHolders are used in conjunction with adapters to efficiently manage and reuse views in RecyclerView.
Each ViewHolder holds references to the views in each item of the RecyclerView to minimize view lookups.

What to include:

* ViewHolder classes that hold references to item views
* Logic to bind data to the individual views in the view holder

Examples:

* HeroViewHolder.kt
* InventoryViewHolder.kt
* GalleryViewHolder.kt

== Example [InventoryViewHolder.kt]
    //imports
    class InventoryViewHolder(binding: ItemInventoryBinding, navController: NavController) :
        RecyclerView.ViewHolder(binding.root) {

        val bindingItem = binding
        val navController = navController

        fun setItemInventory(inventory: Inventory) {
            bindingItem.tvName.text = inventory.name
            bindingItem.tvPrice.text = "$ ${inventory.price}"
            bindingItem.tvQuantity.text = "${inventory.quantity}"

            bindingItem.cvInventory.setOnClickListener {
                val bundle = Bundle()
                bundle.putSerializable("clave", inventory)
                navController.navigate(R.id.action_homeInventoryFragment_to_itemDetailsFragment, bundle)
            }

        }
    }